      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The Liberty gave up a 17-0 run in the second half and lost its second consecutive preseason game to the Phoenix Mercury, by 79-69, last night at Madison Square Garden.</p>
        <p>The Liberty will play Orlando on Wednesday before opening the regular season at Houston on May 29.</p>
        <p>The Liberty led by 41-37 at halftime behind 17 points from its bench, a necessary dimension for a team with one of the league's oldest starting lineups. The Mercury responded with a 17-0 run to take a 65-57 lead with 7 minutes 31 seconds left in the game. Vickie Johnson of the Liberty and Brandy Reed of the Mercury led their teams with 24 points each.</p>
        <p>LENA WILLIAMS</p>
